creator: Alexandre Dumas
description:
LibriVox recording of Louise de la Valliere by Alexandre Dumas.
Read in English by Robert Snoza; Phil Griffiths; Lynne Thompson; deongines; Eden Rea-Hedrick; acousticwave; Wayne Donovan; ToddHW; Gail Timmerman Vaughan; Filippo Gioachin

After The Three Muskateers and Twenty Years After the adventurous story of Athos, Porthos, Aramis and D'Artagnan continues!

The Vicomte of Bragelonne: Ten Years Later (French: Le Vicomte de Bragelonne ou Dix ans plus tard) is the last of the Musketeer novels. It is usually divided into four volumes and this third volume contains chapters 141-208. (Summary by Diana Majlinger)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
